An Act relative to the International Holocaust Remembrance Alliance definition of antisemitism.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 1 of Chapter 151B, as appearing in the 2022 Official Edition, is hereby amended
2 by adding the following new definition: “24. The term ‘Antisemitism’ shall have the same
3 meaning that is endorsed by the International Holocaust Remembrance Alliance, which shall
4 mean a certain perception of Jews, which may be expressed as hatred toward Jews. Rhetorical
5 and physical manifestations of antisemitism are directed toward Jewish or non-Jewish
6 individuals and/or their property, toward Jewish community institutions and religious facilities.”
